AISurv
Advanced AI Surveillance System
Revised System Design and Architecture Document

Design Status: Architecture and interface specification only
Primary Operator Platform: JavaFX desktop control-centre application using AtlantaFX
Target Deployments: Local-first sites with approximately 5 cameras through hybrid commercial/enterprise deployments with 100+ cameras
Current Prototype Baseline: RTSP camera feeds, frame capture, motion detection, person detection, live display, and event logging
Target Deployment Model: Local edge operation with an optional cloud control plane

1. Product Vision

AISurv is a commercial AI-powered CCTV surveillance platform for institutions such as schools, universities, offices, hospitals, estates, warehouses, and multi-building campuses.

The main operator experience is a professional desktop control-centre application built with JavaFX and AtlantaFX. The platform receives RTSP camera feeds, processes selected frames, detects humans and security-relevant behavior, optionally applies governed identity analysis, preserves evidence, stores records, and sends approved alerts to authorised devices.

AISurv must support three deployment requirements:

1. Every monitored site can run camera ingestion, AI processing, operational persistence, evidence storage, and the desktop client locally without depending on an internet connection.
2. Connected commercial deployments can use an optional cloud control plane for tenant and site management, licensing, fleet health, remote event summaries, notifications, software-update metadata, and approved analytics.
3. Enterprise deployments can separate stream ingestion, AI processing, persistence, evidence storage, analytics, notifications, and clients into independently scalable responsibilities while preserving the local-first boundary.

The cloud control plane augments site operation; it does not sit in the critical path for camera capture, detection, local alerts, incident handling, or evidence preservation.

The system is not just a multi-camera viewer. It is an event-driven intelligent surveillance platform with a desktop command-centre interface.

2. Core Architectural Pattern

AISurv uses a Layered Event-Driven Pipeline Architecture.

